Within ninety (90) days of concluding a high-volume horizontal fracturing treatment, the operator of the horizontal well shall complete the chemical disclosure registry form and post the form on the chemical disclosure registry. The following information shall be required to be furnished:
Operator's name;
The date of the high-volume horizontal fracturing treatment;
The county in which the well is located;
The API number for the well;
The well name and number;
The longitude and latitude of the wellhead;
The true vertical depth of the well;
The total water volume used;
Each chemical additive used in the fracturing treatment, including the chemical abstract service number added, if applicable;
The maximum concentration, in percent by mass, of each chemical intentionally added to the base fluid, if applicable; and
The total amount of proppant used, if applicable.
